# Day 27 – Prior Authorization Story Simulator using Claude AI

## Objective

The objective of this task was to build an interactive Prior Authorization Story Simulator that explains the healthcare prior authorization process through a story-based learning experience. The application simplifies complex healthcare workflows using conversations, decision-making, and educational explanations.

## Project Summary

* Application: Prior Authorization Story Simulator
* Technology: HTML, Tailwind CSS, Vanilla JavaScript
* Type: Interactive Story-Based Healthcare Simulator
* Goal: Learn the Prior Authorization process through Rahul's healthcare journey.

## Features Implemented

* Interactive story with 8 chapters
* Rahul and Priya conversation flow
* Progress tracker
* Two choices after every scene
* Educational healthcare explanations
* Insurance review simulation
* Denial and appeal workflow
* Final approval scenario
* Workflow summary and key takeaways
* Responsive user interface
* Restart story functionality

## Story Flow

The simulator covers the following stages:

* Doctor Visit
* Insurance Roadblock
* Understanding Prior Authorization
* Insurance Review
* Denial
* Appeal
* Approval
* Final Takeaways

## Key Learnings

* Learned how Prior Authorization works in a real-world healthcare workflow.
* Understood why documentation and medical necessity are important.
* Explored how denials can be appealed with proper supporting documents.
* Improved interactive storytelling and front-end development skills.
* Learned how AI can make complex healthcare concepts easier to understand.

## Conclusion

This project transformed a complex healthcare process into an engaging interactive story. Claude AI helped create an educational experience that combines storytelling, healthcare knowledge, and web development in a beginner-friendly way.
